# K-Means Clustering

## Overview

K-Means is an unsupervised learning algorithm used to group data into **K clusters**.

The algorithm works by:

1. Choosing K cluster centers
2. Assigning data points to nearest center
3. Updating the cluster centers
4. Repeating until clusters stabilize

## Libraries Used

* pandas
* scikit-learn

## Run

pip install pandas scikit-learn

python kmeans_clustering.py
